11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 6-1, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 6-1. A. The State Veterinarian shall be the holder of:
17 1. Hold a current license to practice veterinary medicine in
18 Oklahoma,;
19 2. Have experience in food animal veterinary practice; and
20 shall be
21 3. Be appointed by the State Board of Agriculture.
22 B. The Board shall fix the compensation and duties of the State
23 Veterinarian.
24 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
